Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}, then peel off the big leaves (3 leaves per person).

Pop the @vegetable spring rolls{4} onto a #baking tray{} and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and piping hot, ~{12-14%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

While the pork fries, drain the @king prawns{225%g}.

Add the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @red Thai style paste{50%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and half the @Thai style spice mix{2%sachet} to a large #saucepan{}. Bring to the boil.

Once boiling, stir in the prawns and simmer for ~{5-6%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

When the mince has browned, stir in the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @ketjap manis{25%g} and remaining Thai style spice blend. Cook for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in a good squeeze of lime juice and half the lime zest. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed, then remove from the heat.

When the prawns are cooked through, stir in the @sugar snap peas{150%g} and simmer until the veg is tender, ~{1-2%minutes} longer. Add a good squeeze of lime juice and remove from the heat. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Meanwhile, cook the @steamed basmati rice{1} according to the pack instructions.

While the rice warms, fill the baby gem leaves with the spiced pork.

Pop the rice in a #serving bowl{}, fluff up with a #fork{} and stir through or sprinkle over the remaining lime zest. Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside.

Serve your prawn curry in a large serving bowl. Transfer your stuffed lettuce cups and spring rolls to separate #serving plates{}.

Add two thirds of the @sweet chilli sauce{144%g} into a #dipping bowl{}, then drizzle the remaining sauce over the pork cups. Finish with the @salted peanuts{40%g}.

Share and tuck in.

Enjoy!